[CMD] /edit UserID: 1115502658539761665, UserTag: nickyster, GuildID: 1500900336674541659, Options: [{"name":"title","type":3,"value":"Palace of Black and White"},{"name":"content","type":3,"value":"{{Notice|title=WANRING!|body=READ THIS IN DARK MODE!}}\n{{Background|file=Palace of black and white 1.png}}\n\nTHE LEGENDARY PALACE.\n{{Class variable}}\n\n== Overall description ==\n[[File:Palace of black and white 1.png|alt=A picture of the level|left|thumb|262x262px|A picture of the level]]\nThis is an enigmatic level called: \"Palace of bl4ck and white\". This palace is around 4 square kilometers long and has a lot of different zones. They all vary in size, shape, safety, stability and other things.\nThis is the spawn point, proven to just be a small area of the whole level. There will be a Faceling, waiting to get you into a carriage and for you to look around thi beautiful palace !\nThere is nothing more for you to do, so get into the carriage and go on the unforgettable tour !\n\n== Zones of the level ==\n\n=== Zone 1 - The Gardens: ===\n{{Class 0 (Customizable)|hexagon=T|class=fresh air|safety=good air|security=stable ground|entity=some secrets|color-s=1000|color-l=-100|color-h=1000}}\nThe first zone of the tour, the Gardens. There are a few different gardens scattered across this level, so lets start with the first and the best garden:\n\n==== Zone 1.1 - The Garden of Es: ====\nThis is the first garden we come across. This garden is pretty big, and, as you can see, is pretty big, we like to call it The Garden of Es, because it is the main reason the residents of the palace can survive in here. In our language it means: \"surviving\". It gives us food, wood and also it has a big pond over there. It is fully ''safe ,'' so there is no need to worry.\n\n==== Zone 1.2 - The Serene Garden ====\nThis is the second most important garden of our palace. This garden was actually red, but now it is bl4ck and white, after the draining incident I will explain later in the tour. It is ''Serene, Beautiful and Perfect.''\n\n==== Zone 1.3 - The danger forest ====\nThis forest is dangerous and contains Manchineel trees and also Walnut trees, but we learnt how to safely collect the sap and use it in a good way, mostly to treat diseases, but also to make beverages.\n\n==== Zone 1.4 - The corrupted forest ====\nThis forest is even more dangerous than the last one. It has glitched trees that emit corrupted particles we collect to use in food and drinks. ''We know what we are doing.''\n\n=== Zone 2 - The palace ===\n{{Class 0 (Customizable)|hexagon=P|color-s=100000|class=Royal|safety=black|security=and|entity=white}}\nWelcome to the Palace! There are different zones in here, and there is a lot of them, so be ready!\n\n==== Zone 2.1 - Bowling alley ====\nThis is the first zone of the palace, strangely it is just a bowling alley. No one visits it, there are even spider webs everywhere. It is still fully functional though!\n\n==== Zone 2.2 - The cafeteria ====\nThis, as the name suggests, is a cafeteria. We have all kinds of foods in here, including fish, cow, chicken, pork, all different kinds of plants and from drinks we sadly only have 4 options: Water, Manchineel juice, Corruption juice, Manchineel twist juice. They are tasty, even though they sound pretty bad.\n\n==== Zone 2.3 - The bathrooms ====\nThis zone is just a bathroom. Just a normal bathroom. Nothing strange or weird.\n\n==== Zone 2.4 - Sports club ====\nHere the residents exercise and have fun 🙂\n\n==== Zone 2.5 - Classrooms ====\nThose are classrooms, mostly for learning math and physics, but there are a lot of other different subjects like: Juice making, fashion and window-making? I still don't know why window-making class exists...\n\n=== Zone 3 - The Throne ===\nWell, my friend, we have arrived at the most important part of this level. The throne. This is the place where the King resides, but he is not here just for this tour! There is nothing more about this zone, so have a good day and bye!\n\nThis was a note found by a person in [[level 11]], given to him by a fancy-looking faceling\n\n== The draining incident ==\nThis incident happened sometime in this palace. The palace was actually colorful before and it was called colorful palace by it's residents, the normal patygoers, but then as more and more partygoers started disappearing, it was found out they were turning into gray, Noir partygoers. Eventually everything turned gray and now there are noir partygoers in there, which are smarter, more calm and weaker physically.\n\n== Anomalies and M.E.G. thoughts ==\nM.E.G. thinks to put this level into class habitable, but because it is unsafe because of the fungi, they don't know how to classify it. They will probably classify that level as a new special class:\n{{Class 0 (Customizable)|hexagon=N|safety=mostly safe, unsafety under control|security=mostly stable, instability under control|entity=no harmful entities, but harmful fungi and plants|class=Noir|color-s=1000}}\n\n== Entities ==\n\n\nEven though it was believed that not much entities are here, it is infested with [[Noir Partygoers]]. Also there might be a lot of different types of fungi, Manchineel trees and Walnut trees and etc. There are around 300 plant/fungi types, most of them are from backrooms and only a few are from Frontrooms.\n\n== Entrances and exits ==\n\n=== Entrances ===\nYou can enter from doing something which we still don't know in [[Th3 Sh4dy Gr3y]]\n\nYou can enter here from any level that is Class 3e or higher\n\n=== Exits ===\nYou can exit to level [[Th3 Sh4dy Gr3y]] or to [[level 71]] if you ask a Noir Partygoer\n\nYou can also exit to [[level Fun]] if you ask a Noir Partygoer\n\nYou can noclip into a Manchineel tree or a Walnut tree to get teleported to [[level 2138]]\n\nYou can noclip into a tree in the Serene garden to get sent to [[Level 14 Rewrite|level 14]]. Who doesn't want paradise?\n\nYou can noclip into a corrupted tree in the corrupted garden to get sent to [[Level -0-D|level -0]]"},{"name":"reason","type":3,"value":"requested"},{"name":"create","type":5,"value":true}]
